Whiskey Creek Country Club - About Skip to Main Content (239)-481-3021 clubmgr@whiskeycreekcc.com Menu Drinks Specials Events Parties Catering Jobs Facebook page Google page Facebook page Google page Toggle navigation Menu Drinks Specials Events Parties Catering Jobs Whiskey Creek Country Club slideshow start stop playing Dot slide navigation number 1 Dot slide navigation number 2 previous slide next slide Whiskey Creek Country Club About us Whiskey Creek Country Club, built in 1974, has seasoned and well developed greens, fairways, tees and bunkers. We welcome you to a unique world that combines a challenging executive golf course with unsurpassed social opportunities. Excellent golf and social membership are available. We are a friendly and affordable golf destination in beautiful South West Florida. WCCC is challenging for low handicaps -  we have over 32 bunkers protecting greens and many trees protecting fairways and greens. You will definitely use every club in your bag. Our par 60 design also makes the course very enjoyable for high handicap golfers. High handicappers will no longer need to lumber through 500 yard par 5's. Our longest hole is 326 from the red tees and 336 from the blue tees which allow golfers of all levels the ability to compete and have fun at Whiskey Creek. Being a par 60 has its privileges! Most 18-hole rounds are completed well under the four hour time frame. The Club is Semi-Private with the public cordially invited. The Club has a full bar serving your favorite beverages seven days a week and restaurant serving a breakfast and lunch menu Tuesday through Sunday and dinner on Tuesday and Friday nights. The Club also has facilities to host your private party, business meeting, family gathering or social event. If you enjoy cards and games, Whiskey Creek has activities that include Mah Jongg, Euchre, Hand and Foot, Bridge and Gin to name a few, along with dinner, dancing and many social events throughout the year. Join us and discover all the beauty and enjoyment WCCC has to offer you and your family. We invite you to come and visit! For more information please contact us at 239 - 481-3021 . Contact us: by phone (239)-481-3021, by email clubmgr@whiskeycreekcc.com Parties Catering Jobs

A unique golf experience which combines a challenging course with 32 bunkers and many trees protecting the fairways and greens. The club is semi-private as it allows public play primarily during the summer months. There is a wide variety of golf membership options from summer membership to an annual membership at an affordable price. In addition to golf, the club offers numerous social opportunities including card games and events. Also, residents and guests have access to a full bar and restaurant. Be sure you hit the clubhouse for your 19th hole! The course is surrounded by single family homes and condos which are not a part of the golf course. Additionally, homeowners may own their own golf cart and pay a trail fee to the club. Leadership - Whiskey Creek Farms Skip to content Operations Grain Farming Livestock Insurance About About Us History Leadership Contact Careers Operations Grain Farming Livestock Insurance About About Us History Leadership Contact Careers Leadership Brian Peterson President Brian founded Whiskey Creek Inc. in 1986 and continues to lead the company’s daily operations. Over time, Whiskey Creek’s activities have grown to include a large grain farming operation, as well as a beef cattle feedlot in Woodbury County, Iowa. 
Brian was the sole founder and owner of Superior Ethanol, a 50 million-gallon ethanol plant, which was acquired by Green Plains Renewable Energy Inc. (GPRE) in 2006. Today he serves on the GPRE board, as he has since 2005, and as chairman of the nomination and corporate governance committee. In the past he has served on GPRE’s nomination, compensation, risk, and audit committee. Brian has a B.S. degree in Agricultural Business from Dordt College. He is married and has four children. His wife, Anita, grew up on a dairy farm outside of Salem, Oregon. Daniel Peterson Chief Financial Officer Before joining the family business in 2008, Daniel served as plant controller and as financial manager at Wells Dairy Inc. in Le Mars, Iowa. He previously held several positions at Gateway Companies, Inc., in North Sioux City, S.D., including financial analyst, accountant and operations finance manager. He currently serves on the board of the Siouxland Economic Development Corporation. Daniel earned a B.A. degree in accounting, management and finance from Northwestern College and an MBA degree from the University of South Dakota. Daniel and his wife, Kim, have four children. Kim is originally from Pella, Iowa. John Peterson Project Management John is responsible for financial and other management projects. He is a grandson of Oscar Peterson, the founder of the family farm in the early 1900s. John is a career agronomist who ran the farm until the mid-1980s, when his son Brian took over operations. After working at Gateway 2000/Gateway Companies, Inc. for several years, John returned to the farm, now known as Whiskey Creek, in 2003. He continues to fill an important role in the financial, logistics, and client and community relations of the operation.  John has a B.S. degree in agri-business from Iowa State University. John and his wife Karen, have seven children and 21 grandchildren. Karen also comes from a Woodbury County farming family. Aaron Peterson Agronomist Aaron is the agronomist for Whiskey Creek’s grain farm operations. He is responsible for sourcing crop inputs, managing in-season pest pressure, and managing the farm management software. Aaron develops site-specific crop plans and works with the company’s feedlot to provide the feedstuffs needed while increasing soil conservation using cover crops, nutrient management and no-till practices. Aaron has a B.S. degree in Ag Business from Iowa State University. Danny Nuno Feedlot Manager Danny  is Whiskey Creek’s feedlot manager. He is responsible for overseeing the health and welfare of the cattle, as well as maximizing the cattle’s growth and efficiency. Danny is also responsible for the feedlot’s bunk management and directing the feed team. 712-943-5304 info@whiskeycreekinc.com Lawton, IA Family Farmers for Five Generations Copyright © 2020 Whiskey Creek Farms | Privacy Policy | Terms of Service | Powered by ladybee
